race.comment: Competitive. BUSTER BIFF (2) jumped quickly to the mile and was too good in Maiden grade after working over to the speed. Doubt this is much harder and he draws inside today. Keeps the handy gate and he looks capable of taking the next step. MISS WALL STREET (1) went close here over 1400m in stronger grade and is ready for the longer distance. The 2kg claim helps offset the weight rise and she's likely to settle back and hit the line hard. TOSEN IMPACT (6) resumed here well supported over a mile, but didn't finish it off. She'd switched from a Victorian stable and was coming off a near miss in a 56 at Tatura this distance range. Has a low gate and WA's top hoop replaces the apprentice. Quick improvement is likely. SNIP OF GOSSIP (3) ran a competitive number beaten a whisker this trip in a 52 at Narrogin and then found the grade much too tough at Ascot.  Needs a good ride but is much better suited.
